---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/docs.astro';
---
<DocsLayout title="Quick Start" current="Quick Start">

<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Quick Start</h1>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Run your first strategic engagement in under a minute.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3">Start an engagement</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Open any terminal and run:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">clawsewitz "Acme Design — subscriber decline, 5%/mo for 3 months, need turnaround"</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">The agent creates a case workspace, sets partner posture, and starts triage — seven intake questions before any analysis. Or launch the interactive REPL with just <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">clawsewitz</code> and use slash commands inside.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="define">What happens next</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">The orchestrator works through nine moves, writing one job-named artefact per move. Moves without signal are skipped — the orchestrator says so out loud when it does.</p>

<div class="flex flex-col gap-3 mt-4 mb-8">
  {[
    { step: 'Intake', file: 'intake.md', desc: 'Seven clarifying questions. Partner read. Trinity stakeholder force-map.' },
    { step: 'Frame', file: 'frame.md', desc: 'Frame the problem using SCQ, HTDQ, or Outcome.' },
    { step: 'Decompose', file: 'decomposition.md', desc: 'MECE decomposition. Validated by the analyst agent. Schwerpunkt named.' },
    { step: 'Research', file: 'research-brief.md', desc: 'Optional. Researcher agent gathers external evidence.' },
    { step: 'Analyse', file: 'analysis.md', desc: 'Run analyses on each leg of the tree using 70+ frameworks.' },
    { step: 'Insights', file: 'insights.md', desc: 'Mount so-whats on page archetypes (Canvas, 2×2, Journey Map). Fog acknowledged.' },
    { step: 'Narrative', file: 'brief.md', desc: 'Writer agent structures Minto Pyramid, SCQA, or StoryBrand. Boldness test.' },
    { step: 'Recommend', file: 'recommendation.md', desc: 'Named option with Ends-Ways-Means. Red-team adversarial review.' },
    { step: 'Plan', file: 'plan.md', desc: 'Implementation plan with friction register, reserves, and premortem.' },
  ].map((s) => (
    <div class="flex gap-4 items-start rounded-lg bg-surface-card p-4">
      <div class="shrink-0 w-24">
        <span class="font-mono text-[13px] font-semibold text-prussian">{s.step}</span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-primary">{s.desc}</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">Produces <code class="font-mono bg-prussian-tint px-1 py-0.5 rounded">{s.file}</code></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="commands">Workflows</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Run from the terminal or as slash commands inside the REPL.</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
  <table class="w-full text-sm">
    <thead>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/10">
        <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold text-text-primary">Terminal</th>
        <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold text-text-primary">REPL</th>
        <th class="text-left py-2 font-semibold text-text-primary">What it does</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz "brief"</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/clawsewitz</code></td><td class="py-2">Full strategic engagement</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz decompose</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/decompose</code></td><td class="py-2">MECE problem decomposition</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz brief</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/brief</code></td><td class="py-2">Executive brief or memo</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz audit</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/audit</code></td><td class="py-2">Red-team + premortem</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz evaluate</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/evaluate</code></td><td class="py-2">Weighted criteria scoring</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz research</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/research</code></td><td class="py-2">Competitive intelligence</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz plan</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/plan</code></td><td class="py-2">Implementation roadmap</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-prussian/5"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">clawsewitz frameworks</code></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/frameworks</code></td><td class="py-2">Browse 70 frameworks</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4"></td><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-prussian">/case</code></td><td class="py-2">Manage case workspaces</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="frameworks">Frameworks</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Look up any of 70 frameworks by name:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-2 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">clawsewitz frameworks "SPADE"</code>
</div>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">/frameworks define</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Each framework comes with a definition, worked example, and step-by-step instructions. The orchestrator picks the right framework for each move based on engagement signals.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="subagents">Agents</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Four specialized agents. The orchestrator dispatches them inline as the engagement unfolds:</p>
<ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-text-secondary flex flex-col gap-2 mb-4">
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Researcher</strong> — hunts for evidence across the web, benchmarks, and competitive landscape</li>
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Analyst</strong> — decomposes problems, applies frameworks, validates MECE integrity</li>
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Writer</strong> — structures findings into briefs, memos, slide narratives, and implementation plans</li>
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Challenger</strong> — stress-tests plans, plays adversary (Red Team), writes the failure narrative (Premortem)</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="hooks">Enforcement</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Built-in guardrails reinforce discipline throughout the engagement:</p>
<ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-text-secondary flex flex-col gap-2 mb-4">
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Auto-commit</strong> — optionally commits every case artefact to git</li>
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Analyst amplifier</strong> — highlights analyst verdicts that flag problems</li>
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Session resume</strong> — surfaces active cases on startup</li>
  <li><strong class="text-text-primary">MECE structural check tool</strong> — quick structural pass before the analyst handles semantics</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3">Resume a case</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Case state persists across sessions. To pick up where you left off:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">/case resume acme-turnaround</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary">The session resume will also surface any active case when you start clawsewitz.</p>

</DocsLayout>
